						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Tiruvandanāthēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Rājanārāyaṇa Śa[m]buvarāya. Year 8: 1346 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The details of the date, <hi rend="italic">viz.</hi>, Monday, <hi rend="italic">dvitīyā</hi> and Aśvati will correspond to 1346 A.D., October 2, Monday, f.d.t. ·37, ·22. The month was Tulā and the <hi rend="italic">paksha</hi> bahuḷa.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary inscription seems to record some gift to a god and goddess (<hi rend="italic">nāyaka-nāchchiyār</hi>) and refers to Madhurāntaka-chaturvēdimaṅgalam.</p>						

						</summary>
